India â€™s LMJ International Ltd. won
a bid to supply 50,000 metric tons of wheat to  Bangladesh , a
government spokesman said today.  The Directorate General of Food, the state grains buyer,
will buy wheat from LMJ International at $303.9 a ton, Nurul
Karim, joint secretary of the Cabinet Division, told Bloomberg
by phone from Dhaka, after a cabinet panel approved the
purchase.  LMJ International became the lowest bidder among six
companies that participated in the tender, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
